Oscar Pistorious dies, what goes around comes around PRETORIA &#8211; South African Paralympic gold medallist, Oscar Pistorious hanged himself in his prison cell where he was serving a jail term for the murder of Reeva Steenkamp, prison officials said on Saturday. Pistorious, 30, was a celebrated Olympian and Paralympic gold medalist before fatally shooting his girlfriend Reeva on Valentine&#8217;s Day in 2013. He was convicted of the killing and sentenced to 6 years in prison a year ago. Staff at the Atteridgeville Correctional Centre in Pretoria, found Pistorious hanging in his prison cell at 5:30 am local time on Sunday. He was taken to a nearby hospital, where he was pronounce dead an hour later. &#8220;Mr. Pistorious hanged himself utilizing a bed sheet that he attached to his cell window,&#8221; the state corrections commission said in a statement. &#8220;Mr. Pistorious also attempted to block his door from the inside by jamming the door with various items.&#8221; His body has since been deposited at the morgue awaiting autopsy.